sent long distances from the coal fired power station. 54% of the retail cost of electricity goes to meet the cost of constructing and maintaining a electricity distribution network of sufficient capacity to deliver power on those days of maximun demand. This is known as the network cost. By reducing how much power must be delivered from the coal fired power station rooftop solar panels reduce that network cost, the largest component of your electricity bill.\nThe", "recommendation_count": "4", "in_reply_to": "114413925", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114426248", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1523017014000}, "author": "Walsunda", "author_id": "12483673", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "\"Yep, of course it included all that maintenance.\"\nYou're confident that are you? Why then was that maintenance not carried out?https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2016/feb/04/hazelwood-mine-manager-charged-with-10-offences-over-morwell-fire\n\"The fact that the new owners sweated the asset isn't overly relevant though.\"https://www.net.au/news/2017-09-04/morwell-residents-seven-times-more-likely-to-have-a-heart-attack/8869874\n\"Balance sheets don't deal with profit.\"\nThe profit and loss statement shows net income, the balance sheet shows what the company is actually worth. Total expenses are subtracted from total revenue, returning a profit or loss. The balance sheet has a few different calculations that are all performed as representations of one basic formula: assets equal liabilities plus owners equity. \nAs you were talking about a depreciating asset sold 25 to 32 years after it was built, balance sheets may be more relevant that the simple profit and loss statement of 1996. As the company was the Government of Victoria who owns and has equity in that company?", "recommendation_count": "4", "in_reply_to": "114413915", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114415063", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1522999819000}, "author": "Stephen Prowse", "author_id":