 Boston in some of the last few years.\nBut if you look at the snow and ice that care about temperature the most, we have less river ice than we used to, less lake ice, less seasonal snow cover, less seasonally frozen ground, less perennially frozen ground, we have smaller glaciers, we have shrinking ice sheets, we have loss of sea ice. \nAll the big pieces of snow and ice which care about temperature are shrinking.", "recommendation_count": "18", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "the world is above average in temperature", "effect": "ice is melting all over the planet"}]}, {"id": "114546645", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1523323591000}, "author": "quokkaZ", "author_id": "4069809", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "A bit more thought suggests this PV cooling is probably an illusion. What is the ultimate fate of the electricity produced from PV panels (or by any other method)? It ends up as heat and in the case of rooftop PV it ends up as heat in the building directly below or just outside the building in the case of aircon. No free lunch.", "recommendation_count": "2", "in_reply_to": "114544576", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114546291", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1523320917000}, "author": "quokkaZ", "author_id": "4069809", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nYes - I am surprised that the Photo Voltic (black panels) cool the surroundings - I would like to know more about that\nBQEND\nYes, I would like to see a proper reference for that too. I would also like to know - compared to what? Bitumen? Concrete? Light coloured roof tiles?\nThe Guardian really should be capable of better reporting than this.", "recommendation_count": "5", "in_reply_to": "114544576", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114545624", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1523317462000}, "author": "greenveggie", "author_id": "12505139", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "And here we see the financial costs of GW rising, unless of course citie