aiming the uncertainties are much smaller than they are. I believe that in court, the scale of these uncertainties will come out. Of course, defenders of CAGW will try hard to avoid discussing the uncertainties. They will focus on arguments to demonstrate 'there is a scientific consensus, so the court shouldn't question it'.", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "114880957", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114885948", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1524117464000}, "author": "Walsunda", "author_id": "12483673", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "While you say I'm correct in saying this is an open discussion board you talk above about \"your thread\" being hijacked. You don't own the thread and if others hijack it to expose what's beneath that's well and good. In a free discussion people can insist that you respond to their questions. While you may think that what they wrote has nothing to do with what you think is your point, they may think otherwise.", "recommendation_count": "7", "in_reply_to": "114865433", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114950565", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1524248066000}, "author": "GoldenAppleCorps", "author_id": "17327071", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "On the basis of your \u2018drinking a gallon of water is the same as driving to work\u2019 argument? Maybe not.", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "114948091", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114884981", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1524111429000}, "author": "Erik Frederiksen", "author_id": "15131989", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "The NY Times articles on global warming are excellent, they have very good journalists.\nMy problem is with the editorial staff which should be running more articles and placing them more prominently.\nThey could also waive fees for these articles.", "recommendation_count": "4", "in_reply_to": "114876025", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114884663", "time_stamp": {"$date": 15