e which the scientific evidence supported, science does not then revise its views about things in general. If there is conflicting expert scientific evidence about a matter in a legal case, I am not aware of instances in which the scientific community would regard the result of those proceedings as in any way a resolution of scientific disputes. But perhaps that\u2019s not quite what you are saying.", "recommendation_count": "15", "in_reply_to": "114878524", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114947074", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1524241090000}, "author": "KingInYellow", "author_id": "3917113", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nAs did the Hutton Enquiry (and a number of others) on Blair's government. Who now believes those enquiries were not a whitewash?\nBQEND\nIncorrect.there were more than nine enquiries into the climate gate manufactrovosy, none of which concluded scientific malpractice.\nIn deeming that multiple institutions globally are colluding, you are drifting into the conspiracy arena.\nAre you trying for a full sweep of denialist bingo ?\nAll the best.", "recommendation_count": "27", "in_reply_to": "114941317", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114947004", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1524240967000}, "author": "KingInYellow", "author_id": "3917113", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nMy own experience is with one of those many national scientific bodies that claim to suport the CAGW case\nBQEND\nCAGW - a non scientific term used only by deniers.\nAnother red flag as to your expertise on this subject goes up.\nBQSTART\nThe 'position statement' was put together by a committee. We members were given no opportunity to provide comment or feedback.\nBQEND\nIncorrect.Over the decades, the scientific bodies hold regular elections to their leading councils, and then to their expert committees.\nIf over decades deniers have failed to get elected to either the councils or committees this indicates they have n