 paper, Ice Melt, Sea Level Rise and Superstorms posited 3 main things:\n1. That sea level rise would likely arrive faster than the consensus science suggested.\n2. That deep ocean circulation, the AMOC and Antarctic bottom water formation, were likely more sensitive to shutdown from fresh meltwater off the ice sheets than previously appreciated.\n3. That there's evidence of superstorms unlike any we have today in Earth's history at temperatures less than 1 degree C above today.\nHis paper caught a lot of flak, but just a few months after publication, another paper came out by Pollard and DeConto which in the words of the glaciologist Richard Alley put some physics behind what Hansen wrote.\nAnd more recently we've see the underside of Antarctica being whittled away faster than we thought, and a measured 15 percent decrease in the AMOC.", "recommendation_count": "2", "in_reply_to": "115057669", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115085202", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1524599605000}, "author": "FeatheredFiend", "author_id": "15683720", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Dissent on what?", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "114876283", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115085057", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1524599215000}, "author": "FeatheredFiend", "author_id": "15683720", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "NMP.\n& good luck with your blinkered dreams.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "114984460", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115083248", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1524595234000}, "author": "loco_p_man", "author_id": "13126382", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "BQSTART\nWell said! ... and their personal agenda, of course\nBQEND\nI am sure that now you have AV's approval, you can consider your job done. Congratulations !", "recommendation_count": "4", "in_reply_to": "115051967", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "115083043", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1524594840000}, "author": "loco_