cratic politics. In the end, through a variety of methods, Webb built a seamless web of political liaisons that brought continued support for and resources to accomplish the Apollo moon landing on the schedule Kennedy had announced. Webb left NASA in October 1968, just as Apollo was nearing a successful completion. It is impossible to conceive of NASA\u2019s success with Apollo had Webb not been in Washington overseeing the politics of the program. \nWebb molded NASA in ways that might not have been anticipated in response to the moon landing mandate. During his tenure the Mercury, Gemini and Apollo programs were carried to fruition.\nBQEND\nand from his Wikipedia page :\nBQSTART\nDespite the pressures to focus on the Apollo program, Webb ensured that NASA carried out a program of planetary exploration with the Mariner and Pioneer space programs.\nBQEND\nIt isn't necessary to have a technical background to be the NASA administrator (though I agree that it is preferable, all other things being equal between candidates).", "recommendation_count": "2", "in_reply_to": "114955225", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "114945367", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1524238137000}, "author": "TTauriStellarbody", "author_id": "16773618", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "I am resolutely proud to stand against the OP, those who upvoted and those who ignored the consaquences.The OP states that climate change will cause mass migration and the result of this will be genocide. \nBQSTART\nWhen the mass migrations start, and social systems fail, those in power will look to powerful and quick solutions. \nOnly an epidemic or war will ultimately solve this problem. \nBQENDOnly.\nThese are your values.\nI take pride in standing against them.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "114944403", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "climate change", "effect": "mass migration and the result of this"}]}, {"id": "114967241", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1524315856000}, "author": "loc